-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-scaled.jpg 2560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-2048x1365.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04102633/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-MTB-mountain-bike-BMX-riding-shoe-Andreu-Lacondeguy-signature-5-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>I liked the original Vice, but I’ve always preferred mid-top designs for most flat pedal use. In addition to the added protection offered by the higher top, the added lacing allows you to run the shoes tight, or loose without feeling like they’re going to fall off your feet. The Vice Mid is unique in that it feels like a slim, relatively light weight skate shoe, yet also feels very protective.</p><p>It also feels incredibly responsive in terms of pedal feel, just like Ride Concepts claims. The outsole just hugs the pedal and transmits every little detail so that you can make micro-adjustments on the pedals without losing your grip. And yet, somehow the shoe feels more supportive than my classic Vans and other shoes with sensitive soles. This is definitely my favorite Ride Concepts shoe yet, and one of my favorite ‘skate’ shoes, period.</p><h2>Colors, Sizing &amp; Pricing</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04110627/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-colors.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04110627/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-colors.jpg\" alt=\"Ride Concepts Vice Mid shoe colors\" width=\"1149\" height=\"610\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1149px) 100vw, 1149px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.ama