2021/03/04110627/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-colors-768x408.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04110627/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-colors-696x370.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04110627/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-colors-1068x567.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/04110627/Ride-Concepts-Vice-Mid-colors-791x420.jpg 791w\"></a></p><p>You have two choices when it comes to color for the Vice Mid. Either classic Black &amp; white, or the Andreu Lacondeguy signature color of Charcoal &amp; Black. Offered in full and half sizes from 7-13 U.S., it’s worth noting that like the Vice, these seem to run about a half size bigger than Ride Concepts’ other shoes. I went down a half size on these to a 41.5 (which is what I wear in most clipless shoes), and the fit is just about perfect.</p><p>Priced at $120, the Vice Mid is available now.</p><p><a href=\"https://rideconcepts.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>rideconcepts.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"0ac6da936d2e9c10119ce78c5873eefe0c30ae4985c000dfce0ed52940550cdd","category":"Cycling"}